author: kfogel
msg: Remove some (probably) obsolete backport branches:
* branches/1.1.x-r13222/: This appears to have been merged to 1.1.x in
r13699, but the merge claims it happened from trunk.  What, then,
was the backport branch for?
* branches/1.1.x-r13358/: This appears to have been merged to 1.1.x in
r13544, but the merge claims it happened from trunk.  Again, what
was the backport branch for?
* branches/1.2.x-r14643/: This was merged into 1.2.x in r14663.  It's
not clear whether merge came from trunk or from the backport branch,
but note that the backport branch did contain the three revisions
that were merged (r14643, r14647, r14650), so it could have been the
source of the merge.
* branches/1.2.x-r14699/: This was merged in r14704.  I'm not sure
what process we should use to replace the generic error with a
non-generic, translated error message, in the 1.2.x line.  But in
any case, I doubt that process would involve this branch.
Note that branches/1.1.x-r14063/ remains; those changes have been
merged into 1.2.x, but not yet into 1.1.x.
